properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued January 8 at 4:06AM CST until January 8 at 10:00AM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...A PERIOD OF LAKE EFFECT SNOW WILL DEVELOP LATE TONIGHT AND
CONTINUE INTO WEDNESDAY MORNING...

.Colder air flowing over Lake Superior has led to some lake effect
snow over northern Iron County and will impact the this mornings
commute for the Kimball, Montreal, Gile, and Hurley areas. This
cold air and breezy winds will also lead to very cold wind chills
this morning across most of northeast Minnesota with readings of
-25 to -35 degrees.

More snow will develop tonight into Thursday. The highest
accumulation is expected along portions of the North Shore which
may see up to 6 inches.

* WHAT...For the Wind Chill Advisory, very cold wind chills. Wind
chills as low as 30 below zero. For the Winter Storm Watch,
mixed precipitation is possible. Total snow accumulations of 3
to 6 inches and ice accumulations of a light glaze possible.

* WHERE...Cook and Lake counties. This includes the Tribal Lands
of the Grand Portage Reservation.

* WHEN...For the Wind Chill Advisory, until 10 AM CST this
morning. For the Winter Storm Watch, from this evening through
Thursday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute. The
dangerously cold wind chills could cause frostbite on exposed
skin in as little as 10 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling. Limit time spent outdoors this
morning. Wear appropriate clothing, a hat, and gloves.

Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM CST THIS MORNING... ...WINTER STORM WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM THIS EVENING THROUGH THURSDAY AFTERNOON
